{"phase":"planning","id":"29-299","detail":"Here is the full investigation report.\n\n---\n\n## Concrete Facts for `internal\/language_tiers` Package (Issue #29)\n\n### Module & Language\n- **Module path**: `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification`\n- **Go version**: `1.25.5`\n- **Build\/test command**: `go test .\/... -count=1` (also `just test`)\n\n### Target Files (do not exist yet)\n- `internal\/language_tiers\/language_tiers.go`\n- `internal\/language_tiers\/language_tiers_test.go`\n\n### Key Dependency: `analysis.ForLanguage`\n\n**Defined at** `internal\/analysis\/analyzer.go:183`:\n\n```go\nfunc ForLanguage(lang string) Analyzer {\n    if factory, ok := registry[lang]; ok {\n        return factory()\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\nReturns a non-nil `Analyzer` for registered languages, `nil` otherwise.\n\n### Registered Languages (with parsers = TierFull)\n\nFound via `init()` registrations in these files:\n\n| Language | Registration line | File |\n|----------|-------------------|------|\n| `\"go\"` | `Register(\"go\", ...)` | `internal\/analysis\/go_analyzer.go:23` |\n| `\"ts\"` | `Register(\"ts\", ...)` | `internal\/analysis\/ts_analyzer.go:25` |\n| `\"js\"` | `Register(\"js\", ...)` | `internal\/analysis\/ts_analyzer.go:26` (shares TS grammar) |\n| `\"py\"` | `Register(\"py\", ...)` | `internal\/analysis\/python_analyzer.go:23` |\n| `\"rs\"` | `Register(\"rs\", ...)` | `internal\/analysis\/rust_analyzer.go:23` |\n\nThe issue says \"go, ts, py, rs\" — but `js` is also registered (same `TSAnalyzer`, same tree-sitter grammar). It will also be TierFull unless explicitly excluded.\n\n### Existing callers of `ForLanguage`\n- `internal\/discovery\/analysis_adapter.go:32` — `analysis.ForLanguage(lang)` to get analyzer for scanning\n- `internal\/engine\/certifier.go:183` — `analysis.ForLanguage(lang)` to decide structural analysis path\n- Test files in `internal\/analysis\/*_test.go` — e.g. `TestForLanguage_Go` and `TestForLanguage_Unknown`\n\n### Tier Concept Already in Doctor\n`internal\/doctor\/doctor.go:642` has `checkAnalysisTiers()` which reports Tier 1 (tree-sitter only) vs Tier 2 (LSP-based). The new package uses a simpler model: **TierFull** (has a registered parser = structural analysis available) vs **TierGeneric** (no parser = file-level metrics only).\n\n### What the Package Must Contain\n\n**`language_tiers.go`:**\n1. A `Tier` type — suggest `type Tier int` with `const` block:\n   - `TierGeneric` (no parser registered)\n   - `TierFull` (has a registered `analysis.Analyzer`)\n2. `func TierForLanguage(lang string) Tier` — calls `analysis.ForLanguage(lang)`, returns `TierFull` if non-nil, `TierGeneric` if nil.\n\n**`language_tiers_test.go`:**\n- Table-driven tests: each of `go`, `ts`, `py`, `rs` → `TierFull`; `\"ruby\"`, `\"swift\"`, `\"c\"`, `\"\"` → `TierGeneric`.\n- Edge case: `js` is also registered — decide whether to include it in the \"supported\" list (the issue says \"go, ts, py, rs\" — but `js` will naturally be TierFull via `analysis.ForLanguage(\"js\")`).\n\n### Non-goals (must NOT touch)\n- `internal\/engine\/scorer.go`\n- `internal\/engine\/pipeline.go`\n- Any report files\n- `internal\/domain\/record.go` (no `Unsupported` field)\n- `Score()` signature\n\n### Existing Test Patterns\nTests in this project use the standard `testing` package with table-driven patterns. Example from `internal\/analysis\/go_analyzer_test.go:336-350`:\n\n```go\nfunc TestForLanguage_Go(t *testing.T) {\n    a := ForLanguage(\"go\")\n    if a == nil {\n        t.Fatal(\"expected Go analyzer\")\n    }\n}\nfunc TestForLanguage_Unknown(t *testing.T) {\n    a := ForLanguage(\"brainfuck\")\n    if a != nil {\n        t.Error(\"expected nil for unknown language\")\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe new test file should follow the same conventions: standard library `testing` only, no external test dependencies.","outcome":{"note":{}},"at":805831821.575642,"ticketId":"29"}
